pd_0_com_3text: What brings you to me today?
pd_1_com_0text: I need your assistance with the case of the murdered Lord Zeppelin.
pd_1_com_1text: It's easier to arrange the facts and evidences in my head when someone's listening.
pd_2_com_0text: Well, what do you want to talk about?
pd_3_com_3text: I need to find more clues.
pd_4_com_0text: So you know who the culprit is? Who did it?
pd_6_com_0text: In this case, the obvious and most likely answer is actually the right one. Lord Zeppelin was murdered by his lovely wife Lady Hot Air Balloon in a not at all lovely way.
pd_7_com_0text: It's quite clear that the general is the murderer.
pd_8_com_0text: This is a tragic case. The young cook wanted to prove his eternal love to his beloved and has gone too far with it.
pd_8_com_1text: That's why he murdered the lord as a " proof of love."
pd_10_com_0text: After the war, things were much worse for the General than they had been before. He is a great warrior, but not a businessman.
pd_10_com_1text: His mismanagement brought his family business to the brink of bankruptcy. But the general is a very proud man and he wanted to avoid this scandal at all costs.
pd_10_com_2text: So he decided to use his influence in order to save his business by illegal means. Tax fraud, moonlighting, he deceived the customers by delivering them worse goods than agreed.
pd_10_com_3text: When Lord Zeppelin learned of this, he demanded that the general bring himself to justice. But probably the general asked him to remain silent or even tried to bribe him.
pd_11_com_0text: And when he refused, he killed him!
pd_12_com_0text: Not quite. At first the general tried to use the invitation to dinner to secretly steal the incriminating materials from the Lord's study.
pd_12_com_1text: But he couldn't find them. All he could find were the Lord's air pressure medications.
pd_12_com_2text: And that's when he decided to murder him!
pd_13_com_1text: You've outdone yourself again, Mr. ShAIRlock Holmes.
pd_14_com_1text: It is one of those instances where the reasoner can produce an effect which seems remarkable to his neighbour, because the latter has missed the one little point which is the basis of the deduction.
pd_14_com_2text: After I managed to find the incriminating documents, the rest was a piece of cake.
pd_14_com_3text: Most of the investigation was probably done by the lord himself.
pd_15_com_0text: You are truly the greatest (living) detective in all of Balloonia, perhaps even the whole world!
pd_16_com_0text: That's unfortunate. But why did she do that?
pd_17_com_0text: Isn't it always the same reason?
pd_17_com_1text: It was about money, of course.
pd_17_com_2text: Lady Hot Air Balloon comes from a simple background, but has become so accustomed to the luxury she got by marrying Lord Zeppelin, that she can't imagine her life without it.
pd_17_com_3text: When she learned that Lord Zeppelin was going to change his will, she became afraid that she would lose everything she possessed and decided to act.
pd_17_com_4text: She knew exactly where to find the Lord's air medication, so she took them and murdered her husband with an overdose.
pd_18_com_0text: All that glitters is not gold.
pd_18_com_1text: You've outdone yourself again, Mr. ShAIRlock Holmes.
pd_18_com_2text: You are truly the greatest detective in all of Balloonia, perhaps even the whole world!
pd_19_com_0text: The most ancient joke in the book.
pd_19_com_1text: But how did you figure that out?
pd_20_com_0text: There are many evidences that led to this conclusion.
pd_20_com_1text: First of all he told me himself that he knew about the Lord's air pressure problem from the very beginning.
pd_20_com_2text: Second, I saved the cook's love letter from the fire, which the lady tried to burn to hide her involvement.
pd_20_com_3text: The third point, however, is the catch. How did he get the medication?
pd_20_com_4text: I'm convinced he got it from Lady Hot Air Balloon.
pd_20_com_5text: But whether she knew of his intention to kill Lord Zeppelin or not, or whether she even incited him to do so, will probably remain a mystery forever.
pd_20_com_6text: What has been proven beyond doubt, however, is that the cook is the murderer!
pd_20_com_7text: And for his crime, he will be brought to justice.
pd_21_com_0text: It is so infuriating that the case could not be fully resolved.
pd_21_com_1text: I know this is gonna keep you bothered for a long time, but there are cases which even the best detective cannot completely resolve.
pd_21_com_3text: Nevertheless, once again you have done an excellent job.
pd_21_com_4text: You are truly the greatest detective in all of Balloonia, perhaps even the whole world!
